    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-01-26T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-01-26T01:00:00-05:00" n="17"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d17">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01 Manchuria/991: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-01-26T15:00:00+09:00"
                            >January 26, 1934—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 26—5:58 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>19. In reply to an interpellation in the Lower House of his views yesterday
                    concerning Hornbeck’s speech Hirota stated that the speech <pb facs="0108"
                        n="18" xml:id="pg_18"/> was not delivered in Hornbeck’s official capacity as
                    the speaker had stressed the point to his audience that he was expressing his
                    private opinion and was not [speaking] for the administration or for the State
                    Department. Furthermore, the version of the speech published in Japan had been
                    distorted and the American Ambassador had corrected the mistake. He wished the
                    members to understand the true situation.</p>
                <p>Copy by mail.<note n="25" xml:id="d17fn25">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
